= Sprint Meeting Minutes (Scrum Master)

Sprint window: Feb 9–Feb 21, 2026  \
Team focus: Reliable onboarding and first complete ride journey.

== Meeting 1 — Feb 9, 2026
- Goal: Set sprint objective and definition of done.
- Sprint goal: Deliver trusted onboarding and unlock ride participation.
- Process agreement: Use short feedback loops with frequent demos.
- Risk: Sign-in and onboarding reliability.
- Action: Track blockers daily and escalate quickly.

== Meeting 2 — Feb 11, 2026
- Goal: Remove scope ambiguity.
- Agreement: Keep sprint focused on MVP outcomes.
- Agreement: Reduce non-essential work to protect timeline.
- Risk: Dependency and integration delays.
- Action: Keep implementation slices small and reviewable.

== Meeting 3 — Feb 13, 2026
- Goal: Check sprint trajectory.
- Status: Core onboarding path is implemented and being stabilized.
- Coaching: Delay feature expansion until core flow is dependable.
- Risk: Completion drops if flow is inconsistent.
- Action: Maintain strict scope discipline.

== Meeting 4 — Feb 16, 2026
- Goal: Burn down highest-priority impediments.
- Blocker: Sign-in reliability issues.
- Blocker: Onboarding completion reliability issues.
- Decision: Freeze non-critical additions until blockers are reduced.
- Action: Re-validate working path after each fix.

== Meeting 5 — Feb 19, 2026
- Goal: Validate first end-to-end user value loop.
- Outcome: Ride lifecycle now supports host and joinee journeys.
- Outcome: Waiting room visibility supports host confidence.
- Process note: Throughput improved after blocker reduction.
- Action: Accept polish work within sprint boundaries.

== Meeting 6 — Feb 21, 2026
- Goal: Close sprint and capture retrospective outcomes.
- Final state: Navigation and host flow are aligned with agreed UX.
- Deliverables: Product flow docs and diagrams completed.
- Retro win: Fast feedback and clear ownership reduced cycle time.
- Carryover: Trust operations and payment guidance refinement.
